# Task 01 — GTM Event Schema (OrthoNow)

## 1. Event Schema

| Event Name | Trigger Type | Key Parameters | Feeds Into (GA4) |
|---|---|---|---|
| `call_now_click` | Click trigger, Just Links, click ID/class contains `call-now-btn` | `page_location`, `click_text` (the phone number), `page_type` (homepage/clinic/landing) | Engagement report, "High-Intent Contact" audience |
| `whatsapp_click` | Click trigger, Click URL contains `wa.me` | `page_location`, `widget_position`, `page_type` | Engagement report, secondary Ads conversion |
| `clinic_page_view` | GA4 Event tag on Page View, deduped against base `page_view` | `clinic_name`, `clinic_id`, `page_location` | Pages & Screens, filtered by clinic |
| `guide_form_submit` | Form Submission trigger if it's a plain POST — more likely a Custom Event trigger since this is a 5-year-old WP build and the form's probably AJAX | `form_name` = patient_guide, `lead_source_page`, `phone_provided` (bool) | Lead gen funnel, "PDF Leads" audience |
| `guide_download` | Custom Event, pushed only after the form succeeds and PDF actually unlocks | `file_name`, `form_name`, `lead_source_page` | Content engagement, download completion vs submits |
| `blog_scroll_depth` | Scroll Depth trigger, 25/50/75/90% | `percent_scrolled`, `article_title`, `article_category` | Engagement, content ROI signal |
| `booking_step_start` | Custom Event, pushed when a step renders | `step_number`, `step_name`, `clinic_location` (if selected already) | Funnel Exploration, entry per step |
| `booking_step_complete` | Custom Event, pushed on validated "Next" click | `step_number`, `step_name`, `clinic_location`, `specialty` | Funnel Exploration, step completion |
| `booking_confirmed` | Custom Event, pushed only after backend confirms — not on the client "Confirm" click | `booking_id`, `clinic_location`, `specialty`, `appointment_date` | Primary conversion, imported to Google Ads |
| `booking_abandoned` (extra, worth adding) | Custom Event via `beforeunload` if user is past step 1 with no completion | `last_step_reached`, `clinic_location`, `time_on_form` | Drop-off diagnostics, remarketing audience |

Naming's snake_case, verb at the end (`_click`, `_submit`, `_complete`) so they sort together in the GA4 events list once there are 15+ of these in the account.

